How ng-template works in angularJs?

ng-template directive is used to create an html view using script tag. It contains "id" attribute which is used by $routeProvider to map a view with a controller.

Syntax:

<script type="text/ng-template" id="templateId.html">
  <p>This is the content of the template</p>
</script>
  <div ng-view></div> // here ng-template content will be displayed
Here, script type is type="text/ng-template" which uses id values to fetch elements and placed it in your ng-view of angularjs.

You can use this id in your your app.js file as:


app.js
=========
var mainApp = angular.module("mainApp", ['ngRoute']);

mainApp.config(['$routeProvider', function($routeProvider) {
   $routeProvider.
   
   when('/addItem1', {
      templateUrl: 'templateId.html', // template id
      controller: 'AddStudentController'
   }).
        
   otherwise({
      redirectTo: '/addItem1'
   });
	
}]);

